- Failed iOS/iPadOS VPP and in-house (`.ipa`) app installs caused by an unresolvable Fleet variable in the managed app configuration (for example, an IdP variable on a host with no IdP linkage) now produce a failed-install activity in the host and global activity feeds, with the specific unresolvable variable shown as the failure reason, instead of being rejected pre-flight (the admin/API path previously returned an HTTP 400 and other paths failed silently).
- Fleet no longer reserves a VPP license seat for an install that fails before reaching the device, releases a reserved seat if the install fails after assignment, and releases a reserved seat when a pending VPP install is canceled, preventing license leaks.
